{"title":"Miss Grape’s ILCOSO Is a Handlebar Bag Cradle & Accessory Mount, All in One","link":"https://bikerumor.com/miss-grapes-ilcoso-handlebar-bag-cradle-accessory-mount-all-in-one/","date":1689861242000,"content":"<p>This looks like a pretty neat product. Italian manufacturer of bikepacking bags, Miss Grape, introduces its new ILCOSO handlebar bag support that’s designed for use with flat or drop bars. After four years of design, development, and testing, this lightweight, modular is not just a “product, but a solution”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"361\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607-800x361.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO front side studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607-800x361.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607-297x134.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607-120x54.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607-768x347.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-front-side-studio-e1689788445607.jpeg 1276w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"528\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815-800x528.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO back side studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815-800x528.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815-297x196.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815-120x79.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815-768x507.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-back-side-studio-e1689788473815.jpeg 853w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125-800x414.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO side view studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125-800x414.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125-297x154.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125-768x397.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-side-view-studio-e1689788427125.jpeg 853w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>ILCOSO is made from PA6 polyamide giving it a combination of compliance and strength while remaining lightweight. The use of polyamide during the construction allows the ICOSO to be safely mounted on carbon or aluminum handlebars. The tube that holds the accessories is made of anodized aluminum.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"822\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463-800x822.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO riding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463-800x822.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463-292x300.jpeg 292w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463-117x120.jpeg 117w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463-768x789.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-riding-e1689788279463.jpeg 853w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. Miss Grape</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Miss Grape states a weight of 320g for the ILCOSO, including long clamps, the accessory tube, and bag holder straps. It was designed to be used with Miss Grape bags, but can also accommodate bags with a maximum recommended diameter of 19cm. It can handle a max load of 3kg (6.6lbs) and fits the handlebar diameter of 31.8 with an 83mm space for the stem clamp to fit. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"483\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966-800x483.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO Mounted and in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966-800x483.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966-297x179.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966-120x72.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966-768x464.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-Mounted-and-in-use-e1689788527966.jpeg 853w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This bag is said to address some of the common issues that other handlebar bags deal with, like cable routing, hand space, contact with the wheel, and compatibility with carbon bars. It places the bag close to the headtube, which Miss Grape says improves steering by moving the load under the stem, where there is the “most space and least bulk”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"433\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397-800x433.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397-800x433.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397-297x161.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397-120x65.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397-768x416.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-in-use-e1689788572397.jpeg 1276w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p> Offering a convenient spot for your instrumentation like your computer, light, bell, or phone, removes all of the bar clutter that could hinder hand placement. All of this, Miss Grape says, “ensures safety and provides a stable, and secure load that does not obstruct visibility of the front wheel”</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>ILCOSO Specs and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empty-on-Yeti.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empty-on-Yeti.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO empty on Yeti\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empty-on-Yeti.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empty-on-Yeti-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empty-on-Yeti-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empty-on-Yeti-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empy.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empy.jpeg\" alt=\"Miss Grape ILCOSO empy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empy.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empy-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empy-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Miss-Grape-ILCOSO-empy-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: € 128.00 ($144)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>ILCOSO comes with: </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>1x Saddlebag holder base bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2x Short Clamps for installation without instrumentation</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2x Long Clamps for installation with instrumentation</li>\n\n\n\n<li>1x Instrumentation holder anodized aluminum tube</li>\n\n\n\n<li>4x 20 mm screws for base clamp fastening</li>\n\n\n\n<li>4x 16 mm screws for instrumentation fastening 2x</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tape lock rings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2x 83cm long saddlebag holder tapes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6x Stickers for clamps</li>\n\n\n\n<li>1x Postcard with QR code to the assembly video</li>\n\n\n\n<li>1x Miss Grape “bunch” sticker</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out the goods below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://missgrape.net/en/\" target=\"_blank\">MissGrape.net</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/miss-grapes-ilcoso-handlebar-bag-cradle-accessory-mount-all-in-one/\">Miss Grape’s ILCOSO Is a Handlebar Bag Cradle &amp; Accessory Mount, All in One</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"775b8089fae026495ac862586b866dc0bc2826f1d0763ea03101df307b28c468","category":"Cycling"}